DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");

$ans1 = random(10,99,1);
$p1 = random(2,9,1);
$a = $p1/100*$ans1;

$ans2 = $ans1*10;
$p2 = $p1/10;

$ans3 = $ans1*100;
$p3 = $p1/100;

Context("LimitedNumeric");
$ans1 = Compute($ans1);
$ans2 = Compute($ans2);
$ans3 = Compute($ans3);

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Fill in the blanks:

a)    [`[$a]`] is  [`[$p1]%`] of [____]{$ans1}?

b)    [`[$a]`] is  [`[$p2]%`] of [____]{$ans2}?

c)    [`[$a]`] is  [`[$p3]%`] of [____]{$ans3}?

END_PGML

##############################################

$s1 = $p1/100;
$s2 = $p2/100;
$s3 = $p3/100;

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

This translation from English to math may help you remember the percentage formula.

    [` 2 \text{ is } 50% \text{ of } 4 \Longleftrightarrow 2 = 0.5 \cdot 4 `]

a)  [`[$a]`] is  [`[$p1]%`] of what?

    [`
\begin{aligned}
  [$a] &= [$s1] \cdot x \\
  \frac{[$a]}{[$s1]} &= \frac{[$s1] \cdot x}{[$s1]} \\
  [$ans1] &= x\\
  x &= [$ans1]
\end{aligned}
    `]

    So [`[$a]`] is [`[$p1]%`] of [` [$ans1] `].  
----
b)  [`[$a]`] is  [`[$p2]%`] of what?

    [`
\begin{aligned}
  [$a] &= [$s2] \cdot x \\
  \frac{[$a]}{[$s2]} &= \frac{[$s2] \cdot x}{[$s2]} \\
  [$ans2] &= x\\
  x &= [$ans2]
\end{aligned}
    `]

    So [`[$a]`] is [`[$p2]%`] of [` [$ans2] `].  
----
c)  [`[$a]`] is  [`[$p3]%`] of what?

    [`
\begin{aligned}
  [$a] &= [$s3] \cdot x \\
  \frac{[$a]}{[$s3]} &= \frac{[$s3] \cdot x}{[$s3]} \\
  [$ans3] &= x\\
  x &= [$ans3]
\end{aligned}
    `]

    So [`[$a]`] is [`[$p3]%`] of [` [$ans3] `].  

END_PGML_SOLUTION

